trans-unit.source: The <languageKeyword>Create Definition</languageKeyword> operation creates a new definition for a specified profile.
trans-unit.target: The <languageKeyword>Create Definition</languageKeyword> operation creates a new definition for a specified profile.

trans-unit.source: This definition will be assigned a version number by the service.
trans-unit.target: This definition will be assigned a version number by the service.

trans-unit.source: For more information about creating a profile, see <link xlink:href="3870699a-09c1-414b-8d42-d8d7c0fde422" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Create Profile</link>.
trans-unit.target: For more information about creating a profile, see <link xlink:href="3870699a-09c1-414b-8d42-d8d7c0fde422" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Create Profile</link>.

trans-unit.target: Request

trans-unit.source: The <languageKeyword>Create Definition</languageKeyword> request is specified as follows.
trans-unit.target: The <languageKeyword>Create Definition</languageKeyword> request is specified as follows.

trans-unit.source: Replace <codeInline>%%amp;lt;subscription-id%%amp;gt;</codeInline> with the subscription ID and <codeInline>%%amp;lt;profile-name%%amp;gt;</codeInline> with the profile name.
trans-unit.target: Replace <codeInline>%%amp;lt;subscription-id%%amp;gt;</codeInline> with the subscription ID and <codeInline>%%amp;lt;profile-name%%amp;gt;</codeInline> with the profile name.

trans-unit.source: For example <embeddedLabel>myapp-trafficmanager-net</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: For example <embeddedLabel>myapp-trafficmanager-net</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: TimeToLiveInSeconds
trans-unit.target: TimeToLiveInSeconds

trans-unit.source: Specifies the DNS Time-to-Live (TTL) that informs the Local DNS resolvers how long to cache DNS entries.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the DNS Time-to-Live (TTL) that informs the Local DNS resolvers how long to cache DNS entries.

trans-unit.source: The value is an integer from 30 through 999,999.
trans-unit.target: The value is an integer from 30 through 999,999.

trans-unit.source: IntervalInSeconds
trans-unit.target: IntervalInSeconds

trans-unit.source: Specifies the number of seconds between consecutive attempts to check the status of a monitoring endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the number of seconds between consecutive attempts to check the status of a monitoring endpoint.

trans-unit.source: The value must be set to 30.
trans-unit.target: The value must be set to 30.

trans-unit.source: TimeoutInSeconds
trans-unit.target: TimeoutInSeconds

trans-unit.source: Specifies the time to wait for response from the monitoring endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the time to wait for response from the monitoring endpoint.

trans-unit.source: The value must be set to 10.
trans-unit.target: The value must be set to 10.

trans-unit.source: ToleratedNumberOfFailures
trans-unit.target: ToleratedNumberOfFailures

trans-unit.source: Specifies the number of consecutive failures to probe an endpoint before taking the endpoint out of rotation.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the number of consecutive failures to probe an endpoint before taking the endpoint out of rotation.

trans-unit.source: The value must be set to 3.
trans-unit.target: The value must be set to 3.

trans-unit.source: Protocol
trans-unit.target: Protocol

trans-unit.source: Specifies the protocol to use to monitor endpoint health.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the protocol to use to monitor endpoint health.

trans-unit.source: Possible values are:
trans-unit.target: Possible values are:

trans-unit.source: HTTP
trans-unit.target: HTTP

trans-unit.source: HTTPS
trans-unit.target: HTTPS

trans-unit.source: Port
trans-unit.target: Port

trans-unit.source: Specifies the port used to monitor endpoint health.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the port used to monitor endpoint health.

trans-unit.source: Accepted values are integer values greater than 0 and less or equal to 65,535.
trans-unit.target: Accepted values are integer values greater than 0 and less or equal to 65,535.

trans-unit.source: Verb
trans-unit.target: Verb

trans-unit.source: Specifies the verb to use when making an HTTP request to monitor endpoint health.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the verb to use when making an HTTP request to monitor endpoint health.

trans-unit.source: The value must be set to GET.
trans-unit.target: The value must be set to GET.

trans-unit.source: RelativePath
trans-unit.target: RelativePath

trans-unit.source: Specifies the path relative to the endpoint domain name to probe for health state.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the path relative to the endpoint domain name to probe for health state.

trans-unit.source: Restrictions are:
trans-unit.target: Restrictions are:

trans-unit.source: The path must be from 1 through 1000 characters.
trans-unit.target: The path must be from 1 through 1000 characters.

trans-unit.target: It must start with a forward slash <codeEntityReference>/</codeEntityReference>.

trans-unit.target: It must contain no brackets <codeEntityReference>%%amp;lt;%%amp;gt;</codeEntityReference>.

trans-unit.source: It must contain no double slashes <codeEntityReference>//</codeEntityReference>.
trans-unit.target: It must contain no double slashes <codeEntityReference>//</codeEntityReference>.

trans-unit.source: It must be a well-formed URI string.
trans-unit.target: It must be a well-formed URI string.

trans-unit.source: ExpectedStatusCode
trans-unit.target: ExpectedStatusCode

trans-unit.source: Specifies the HTTP status code expected from a healthy endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the HTTP status code expected from a healthy endpoint.

trans-unit.source: The endpoint is considered unhealthy otherwise.
trans-unit.target: The endpoint is considered unhealthy otherwise.

trans-unit.source: The value must be set to 200.
trans-unit.target: The value must be set to 200.

trans-unit.source: LoadBalancingMethod
trans-unit.target: LoadBalancingMethod

trans-unit.source: Specifies the load balancing method to use to distribute connection.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the load balancing method to use to distribute connection.

trans-unit.source: Possible values are:
trans-unit.target: Possible values are:

trans-unit.source: Performance
trans-unit.target: Performance

trans-unit.source: Failover
trans-unit.target: Failover

trans-unit.source: RoundRobin
trans-unit.target: RoundRobin

trans-unit.source: Endpoints
trans-unit.target: Endpoints

trans-unit.source: Encapsulates the list of Azure Traffic Manager endpoints.
trans-unit.target: Encapsulates the list of Azure Traffic Manager endpoints.

trans-unit.source: You can define up to 100 endpoints in the list.
trans-unit.target: You can define up to 100 endpoints in the list.

trans-unit.source: If the load balancing method is set to <languageKeyword>Failover</languageKeyword>, traffic to the endpoints is load balanced in the sequential order in which the endpoints are defined.
trans-unit.target: If the load balancing method is set to <languageKeyword>Failover</languageKeyword>, traffic to the endpoints is load balanced in the sequential order in which the endpoints are defined.

trans-unit.source: DomainName
trans-unit.target: DomainName

trans-unit.source: Specifies the endpoint domain name.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the endpoint domain name.

trans-unit.source: The value depends on endpoint type.
trans-unit.target: The value depends on endpoint type.

trans-unit.source: If Type is CloudService, the value must be a fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of a cloud service that belongs to the subscription ID that owns the definition.
trans-unit.target: If Type is CloudService, the value must be a fully qualified domain name (FQDN) of a cloud service that belongs to the subscription ID that owns the definition.

trans-unit.source: If Type is AzureWebsite, the value must be an FQDN of an Azure web site that belongs to the subscription ID that owns the definition.
trans-unit.target: If Type is AzureWebsite, the value must be an FQDN of an Azure web site that belongs to the subscription ID that owns the definition.

trans-unit.source: If Type is Any, the value can be any FQDN for an Azure service or a service outside of Azure.
trans-unit.target: If Type is Any, the value can be any FQDN for an Azure service or a service outside of Azure.

trans-unit.source: Status
trans-unit.target: Status

trans-unit.source: Specifies the status of the monitoring endpoint.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the status of the monitoring endpoint.

trans-unit.source: If set to <languageKeyword>Enabled</languageKeyword>, the endpoint is considered by the load balancing method and is monitored.
trans-unit.target: If set to <languageKeyword>Enabled</languageKeyword>, the endpoint is considered by the load balancing method and is monitored.

trans-unit.target: Possible values are:

trans-unit.target: Type

trans-unit.source: Optional.
trans-unit.target: Optional.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the type of endpoint being added to the definition.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the type of endpoint being added to the definition.

trans-unit.source: Possible values are:
trans-unit.target: Possible values are:

trans-unit.target: If there is more than one <embeddedLabel>AzureWebsite</embeddedLabel> endpoint, they must be in different datacenters.

trans-unit.source: This limitation doesn’t apply to cloud services.
trans-unit.target: This limitation doesn’t apply to cloud services.

trans-unit.target: The default value is <embeddedLabel>CloudService</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.target: MinChildEndpoints

trans-unit.source: Optional.
trans-unit.target: Optional.

trans-unit.source: Can be specified when <embeddedLabel>Type</embeddedLabel> is set to <embeddedLabel>TrafficManager</embeddedLabel>.
trans-unit.target: Can be specified when <embeddedLabel>Type</embeddedLabel> is set to <embeddedLabel>TrafficManager</embeddedLabel>.

trans-unit.source: The minimum number of healthy endpoints within a nested profile that determines whether any of the endpoints within that profile can receive traffic.
trans-unit.target: The minimum number of healthy endpoints within a nested profile that determines whether any of the endpoints within that profile can receive traffic.

trans-unit.source: Weight
trans-unit.target: Weight

trans-unit.source: Optional.
trans-unit.target: Optional.

trans-unit.source: Specifies the priority of the endpoint in load balancing.
trans-unit.target: Specifies the priority of the endpoint in load balancing.

trans-unit.source: The higher the weight, the more frequently the endpoint will be made available to the load balancer.
trans-unit.target: The higher the weight, the more frequently the endpoint will be made available to the load balancer.

trans-unit.source: The value must be greater than 0.
trans-unit.target: The value must be greater than 0.

trans-unit.source: For endpoints that do not specify a weight value, a default weight of 1 will be used.
trans-unit.target: For endpoints that do not specify a weight value, a default weight of 1 will be used.
